  "chapter": {
    "number": 50,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel’s Sin"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Where is your mother’s certificate of divorce",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with which I sent her away?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Or to which of My creditors",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "did I sell you?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Look, you were sold for your iniquities,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and for your transgressions your mother was sent away.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why was no one there when I arrived?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Why did no one answer when I called?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Is My hand too short to redeem you?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Or do I lack the strength to deliver you?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Behold, My rebuke dries up the sea;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I turn the rivers into a desert;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the fish rot for lack of water",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and die of thirst.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I clothe the heavens in black",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and make sackcloth their covering.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Servant’s Obedience"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The Lord GOD has given Me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the tongue of discipleship,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to sustain the weary with a word.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He awakens Me morning by morning;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He awakens My ear to listen as a disciple.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The Lord GOD has opened My ears,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I have not been rebellious,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "nor have I turned back.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I offered My back to those who struck Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and My cheeks to those who tore out My beard.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I did not hide My face from scorn and spittle.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Because the Lord GOD helps Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have not been disgraced;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "therefore I have set My face like flint,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I know that I will not be put to shame.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The One who vindicates Me is near.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who will dare to contend with Me?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let us confront each other!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Who has a case against Me?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Let him approach Me!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely the Lord GOD helps Me.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who is there to condemn Me?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "See, they will all wear out like a garment;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the moths will devour them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who among you fears the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and obeys the voice of His Servant?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Who among you walks in darkness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and has no light?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let him trust in the name of the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let him lean on his God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, all you who kindle a fire,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who array yourselves with firebrands,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "walk in the light of your fire",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and of the firebrands you have lit!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "This is what you will receive from My hand:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You will lie down in a place of torment.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
  },
